MBOMBELA – Eager grade ones filled Laerskool Laeveld’s classrooms ready for big school. There were no tears for this year’s class, as the pupils went to the school on Tuesday with their parents to get acquainted with it and its teachers. A few were still nervous to join their classmates, as they missed home.La  This year, Laerskool Laeveld boasts two sets of twins; Ron and Monica Malatjie and Kayla and Angela Correia. Both sets are in the English classes. At time of writing, the school still had children waiting to be placed. Promises of being called back at 11:00 did not ease parents’ nerves, as they hoped for a positive outcome.